00:19:58,946 --> 00:20:01,435
want their beloved troupe

288
00:20:01,942 --> 00:20:04,306
to end up because of money.

289
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,567
This insurance

290
00:20:07,226 --> 00:20:08,908
is not about money

291
00:20:09,212 --> 00:20:11,141
but it is a proof of belief

292
00:20:11,851 --> 00:20:14,262
that your parents leave for you.

293
00:20:15,174 --> 00:20:16,474
They had a belief that

294
00:20:17,437 --> 00:20:19,237
you guys will not give up,

295
00:20:19,491 --> 00:20:21,861
no matter what the problems you face.

296
00:20:27,866 --> 00:20:28,666
Father.

297
00:20:31,266 --> 00:20:32,866
He always prepare everything for us.

298
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,637
I want to use this money

299
00:20:41,172 --> 00:20:42,320
for paying our debt.

300
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:47,000
And we will find another five hundred thousand

301
00:20:48,866 --> 00:20:50,300
to clear all of our debt.

302
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:55,503
For me,

303
00:20:56,466 --> 00:20:58,668
I will help you by building a stage.

304
00:20:58,668 --> 00:21:00,151
No need to hire others.

305
00:21:00,151 --> 00:21:02,820
This time, I will be the chief craftsman,

306
00:21:03,225 --> 00:21:04,771
build everything by myself.

307
00:21:07,078 --> 00:21:09,078
Appreciate you a lot, uncle.

308
00:21:09,975 --> 00:21:10,708
Don't worry.

309
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,592
Your face…

310
00:22:05,845 --> 00:22:07,767
Is there any good news?

311
00:22:09,466 --> 00:22:10,184
Ding!

312
00:22:10,589 --> 00:22:12,048
We found money from father's insurance

313
00:22:12,048 --> 00:22:13,571
and it will be paid for the debt.

314
00:22:14,917 --> 00:22:21,732
Yay!

315
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:23,262
P'Phet, you know,

316
00:22:23,485 --> 00:22:25,485
You are a MVP

317
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:27,242
P'Phet

318
00:22:28,376 --> 00:22:30,376
We don't debt anymore, right?

319
00:22:30,834 --> 00:22:32,074
Yes, Ploy.

320
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,566
Uncle Thor give me this document by himself.

321
00:22:38,178 --> 00:22:40,066
It not exactly a miracle,

322
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:41,844
but it is

323
00:22:41,844 --> 00:22:44,200
a plan that our parents prepared for us years ago.

324
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:47,100
It sounds like a screenplay,

325
00:22:47,666 --> 00:22:49,443
but it really happens to our family,

326
00:22:49,443 --> 00:22:50,300
Ploy.

327
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,716
So,

328
00:22:53,716 --> 00:22:54,642
are we fully

329
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:56,358
free from debt?

330
00:22:56,561 --> 00:22:57,507
Like officially?

331
00:22:57,507 --> 00:22:59,553
Is it confirm, like CF?

332
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,133
So can we have Mookrata for ten portions?

333
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,000
Ten portions?

334
00:23:05,266 --> 00:23:06,066
Mookrata!

335
00:23:06,133 --> 00:23:06,933
Mookrata!

336
00:23:06,966 --> 00:23:08,533
Mookrata!

337
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:09,400
Enough.

338
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,666
If it still lack of stove,

339
00:23:11,666 --> 00:23:13,500
I can light a fire in the middle of courtyard.

340
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,166
Don't make it like a Boy Scout's campfire.

341
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:19,933
I will buy pork.

342
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,000
I will buy vegetable.

343
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,333
I will set the table.

344
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,133
That's great.

345
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:25,500
So you guys go to buy pork,

346
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:28,200
But don't eat ahead of everyone like last time.

347
00:23:28,766 --> 00:23:30,404
We won't,

348
00:23:30,404 --> 00:23:32,966
unless Khun Pleng Chai steal mine like before.

349
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:35,392
You stole his food?

350
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:36,800
Me?

351
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,200
You don't know?

352
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,392
Thank you, all of you.

353
00:23:41,797 --> 00:23:43,985
From now on, our troupe will not in debt anymore.

354
00:23:44,897 --> 00:23:46,288
and after this,

355
00:23:46,846 --> 00:23:47,678
we

356
00:23:48,083 --> 00:23:50,505
will not leave our troupe behind aGuyn.

357
00:23:50,666 --> 00:23:52,200
Never.

358
00:23:53,166 --> 00:23:54,266
We have no debt.

359
00:23:54,563 --> 00:23:56,563
Yay!

360
00:24:11,662 --> 00:24:18,427
No more debt. No more debt.

361
00:24:24,873 --> 00:24:26,265
Mookrata

362
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,400
Oh.

363
00:24:34,166 --> 00:24:35,700
This is burnt.

364
00:24:35,966 --> 00:24:36,924
It turns as black as coal.

365
00:24:36,924 --> 00:24:37,666
No,

366
00:24:38,166 --> 00:24:39,200
it does not burnt,

367
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,136
it is

368
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:42,837
applied Thai smoked pork,

369
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,166
special recipe of our troupe.

370
00:24:45,166 --> 00:24:45,699
Here.

371
00:24:45,699 --> 00:24:47,000
If it is really a special formula/recipe,

372
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,566
there need to be a caution

373
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:49,366
"Do not eat"

374
00:24:49,366 --> 00:24:50,300
If you have it,

375
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:51,800
it can be fatal.

376
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,400
I don't believe it, you try first.

377
00:24:54,666 --> 00:24:55,466
Eat. Have it.

378
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:57,333
Prove it.

379
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,416
Here, your favorite.

380
00:25:02,416 --> 00:25:02,966
No fat.

381
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:03,900
No burnt.

382
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:06,490
Thank you, Chef Nine.

383
00:25:07,250 --> 00:25:08,675
Besides boiled rice with pork,

384
00:25:09,739 --> 00:25:12,050
I never know that you also good at Mookrata.

385
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:13,500
Eww.

386
00:25:14,733 --> 00:25:15,533
Even Mookrata turns sweet.

387
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:16,862
Yuck.

388
00:25:17,166 --> 00:25:19,866
This leading couple always has their sweet air-time.

389
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:22,018
What about us, second lead?

390
00:25:22,018 --> 00:25:23,866
When will we have air-time like them?

391
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:27,800
You just all talk and only eating next to me.

392
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:31,300
How can we get the air-time? Feed me!

393
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:33,066
Here. Here.

394
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:39,900
It's hot.

395
00:25:40,533 --> 00:25:41,766
Don't tell me you gonna eat it?

396
00:25:43,966 --> 00:25:44,951
It still hot.

397
00:25:44,951 --> 00:25:45,700
I don't want it!

398
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:46,400
Just kidding.

399
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,133
I don't want it.

400
00:25:47,133 --> 00:25:47,933
Look, P'Phet,

401
00:25:47,933 --> 00:25:48,466
It's hot.

402
00:25:48,466 --> 00:25:50,166
They are acting like kids.

403
00:25:52,766 --> 00:25:55,513
Because of their laughs,

404
00:25:55,969 --> 00:25:57,260
that's why our troupe still exist.

405
00:25:59,533 --> 00:26:00,411
Yes, P'Phet.

406
00:26:01,019 --> 00:26:03,656
Their laughs and their trust.

407
00:26:04,766 --> 00:26:05,566
That's great.

408
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,066
Let's eat. Here, get some.

409
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:22,651
Oh, P'Plub.

410
00:26:22,651 --> 00:26:23,480
Have a seat.

411
00:26:23,923 --> 00:26:24,620
Hello.

412
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:25,728
Hi.

413
00:26:25,728 --> 00:26:26,305
(Ploy Ying) Hello.

414
00:26:26,305 --> 00:26:29,137
(Lynchee) You come with desserts.

415
00:26:29,500 --> 00:26:31,333
You called me and said you want macarons,

416
00:26:31,466 --> 00:26:32,733
I bought a lot of them,

417
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:34,466
you guys can also have them too.

418
00:26:37,733 --> 00:26:40,200
Best sweet-brother of the year.

419
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:43,866
Hey, wait a sec.

420
00:26:44,266 --> 00:26:46,100
P'Phet, you are not a fan of desserts, are you?

421
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:55,000
Me. Me. I love it.

422
00:26:58,666 --> 00:26:59,733
Me too. Me too.

423
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:02,133
Would you like to try some, Ploy?

424
00:27:02,766 --> 00:27:03,566
Ah.

425
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:04,766
(Lynchee) Don't take mine.

426
00:27:04,766 --> 00:27:05,266
Oh.

427
00:27:05,266 --> 00:27:06,766
Lynchee really love macarons.

428
00:27:07,733 --> 00:27:08,533
Thank you so much.

429
00:27:09,266 --> 00:27:11,666
I heard you guys have a lot going on lately.

430
00:27:12,133 --> 00:27:15,133
If you have desserts, they might boost your energy.

431
00:27:16,533 --> 00:27:17,333
That's great.

432
00:27:17,766 --> 00:27:19,100
It looks so good.

433
00:27:19,366 --> 00:27:20,200
Eat a lot.

434
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:21,200
Thanks.

435
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:24,133
These desserts seem too special, uh?

436
00:27:29,666 --> 00:27:30,725
Of course they are special,

437
00:27:31,181 --> 00:27:33,100
they are for a person making the troupe special.

438
00:27:38,466 --> 00:27:40,825
Um… Grab your pork and cheers.

439
00:27:40,825 --> 00:27:43,897
Here. Here.

440
00:27:44,607 --> 00:27:46,205
Here. One for each.

441
00:27:46,205 --> 00:27:47,083
Here. Here.

442
00:27:47,387 --> 00:27:48,497
For the auspicious occasion,

443
00:27:48,801 --> 00:27:51,369
No debt, just Mookrata and happiness

444
00:27:51,876 --> 00:27:56,058
Wait, and also desserts from P'Plub.

445
00:27:58,795 --> 00:28:01,115
Cheers!

446
00:28:03,145 --> 00:28:04,300
Would you like to try some, P'Phet.

447
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:05,666
It look really good.

448
00:28:07,566 --> 00:28:08,800
If you feed me,

449
00:28:09,166 --> 00:28:10,500
I can eat anything.

450
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,100
Then eat pork.

451
00:28:25,066 --> 00:28:25,866
Eat a lot.

452
00:28:26,766 --> 00:28:27,566
Don't left over.

453
00:28:32,933 --> 00:28:37,315
Mookrata pop pop. Mookrata pop pop.

454
00:28:37,612 --> 00:28:38,974
Pop pop.

455
00:28:38,974 --> 00:28:39,707
Ugh.

456
00:28:40,444 --> 00:28:41,648
That's so off-key.

457
00:28:42,408 --> 00:28:43,582
Would you like some lemonade?

458
00:28:45,407 --> 00:28:46,471
That's remind me of our mother.

459
00:28:48,042 --> 00:28:50,318
She always told me like that when I was young,

460
00:28:51,166 --> 00:28:53,666
"You should sing in tune and then be a Likay."

461
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:57,700
You really tone-deaf back then.

462
00:29:01,900 --> 00:29:03,366
It makes me missing that house.

463
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:11,368
I think

464
00:29:12,635 --> 00:29:13,985
it quite strange.

465
00:29:15,708 --> 00:29:16,708
Even our parents were gone,

466
00:29:18,178 --> 00:29:22,752
we still have this house and troupe members.

467
00:29:24,366 --> 00:29:25,569
It makes us feel like

468
00:29:26,127 --> 00:29:27,146
we still have a family.

469
00:29:27,501 --> 00:29:28,187
Agree?

470
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,455
Umm, I also share the same thought.

471
00:29:32,519 --> 00:29:34,642
If we were not with the troupe,

472
00:29:35,504 --> 00:29:39,554
we might grow up without anyone to fight with.

473
00:29:40,900 --> 00:29:42,166
But you fought with me?

474
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:43,733
Fighting with you is like exercising.

475
00:29:44,300 --> 00:29:45,800
Sweating every time we argue.

476
00:29:45,966 --> 00:29:47,300
That's true.

477
00:29:48,100 --> 00:29:49,700
Fight everyday,

478
00:29:50,166 --> 00:29:51,000
like exercising everyday.

479
00:29:51,866 --> 00:29:52,700
It's good though.

480
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,400
To have someone to bicker with.

481
00:29:55,533 --> 00:29:56,366
It feels accompanied.

482
00:30:05,766 --> 00:30:06,900
Thank you, P'Ploy,

483
00:30:09,466 --> 00:30:11,733
for not leaving this house behind.

484
00:30:14,566 --> 00:30:16,000
If I don't have you,

485
00:30:18,166 --> 00:30:19,466
I might forget that

486
00:30:20,133 --> 00:30:22,366
Likay can bring this much happiness to us.

487
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:28,354
Well said,

488
00:30:29,013 --> 00:30:30,600
Then you should do the dishes everyday.

489
00:30:30,766 --> 00:30:31,266
Hey,

490
00:30:31,266 --> 00:30:32,966
I keep holding this for a while, can you wash them?

491
00:30:33,100 --> 00:30:35,400
Wait a sec, I need to tie my shoelace. Hold them for me.

492
00:30:35,866 --> 00:30:38,900
I have only two hands, what if they fall and break?

493
00:30:39,066 --> 00:30:39,866
I'm out.

494
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:42,166
Pleng, I can't move. They're too heavy.

495
00:30:47,566 --> 00:30:50,000
♪ For you to know ♪

496
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:53,101
♪ Spark of love shining ♪

497
00:30:54,064 --> 00:30:55,955
♪ Through the heart ♪

498
00:31:11,300 --> 00:31:12,100
P'Phet,

499
00:31:12,566 --> 00:31:13,900
I want to talk with you.

500
00:31:17,700 --> 00:31:18,600
I have been waiting

501
00:31:20,533 --> 00:31:21,992
the moment that two of us

502
00:31:23,310 --> 00:31:24,997
finally open up to each other.

503
00:31:31,533 --> 00:31:32,733
You chased me

504
00:31:34,900 --> 00:31:36,800
because I will be useless to you

505
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:40,133
if I'm not playing Likay, right?

506
00:31:46,317 --> 00:31:47,022
Okay.

507
00:31:47,866 --> 00:31:48,966
Then I will go.

508
00:31:52,466 --> 00:31:53,466
Guy. Guy.

509
00:31:56,566 --> 00:31:57,750
I am sorry that

510
00:31:58,966 --> 00:32:00,249
my words are so harsh to you on that day.

511
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:03,666
I knew that you tired,

512
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,266
But I still stubborn.

513
00:32:09,366 --> 00:32:10,466
There is no need to apologize.

514
00:32:12,266 --> 00:32:13,957
Because of me, I did not finish the sentence that

515
00:32:15,123 --> 00:32:16,560
I could not

516
00:32:17,726 --> 00:32:19,318
be more proud of you.

517
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:26,341
I know at first,

518
00:32:27,558 --> 00:32:28,584
since you were young,

519
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,184
that you don't want to be a Likay, like me.

520
00:32:34,009 --> 00:32:37,096
Every time you watch TV or talk about actors,

521
00:32:37,349 --> 00:32:40,548
I saw your eyes filled with spark,

522
00:32:42,366 --> 00:32:45,900
the spark that I don't have.

523
00:32:49,533 --> 00:32:50,333
P'Phet,

524
00:32:50,766 --> 00:32:51,800
I want to be an actor

525
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:53,933
and act in drama.

526
00:32:56,566 --> 00:32:58,850
Guy, it's probably not a good idea.

527
00:32:59,458 --> 00:33:00,480
People like us

528
00:33:01,190 --> 00:33:03,154
are better performing on the stage.

529
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:06,507
What if

530
00:33:07,774 --> 00:33:10,000
my heart kept dreaming about it,

531
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,666
will you listen to my dream?

532
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:18,700
It is good to have a dream, Guy.

533
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:22,533
Before that, I want you to be able to dance.

534
00:33:23,133 --> 00:33:23,933
Come.

535
00:33:24,466 --> 00:33:25,733
Follow my dance pattern.

536
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:29,533
Like this.

537
00:33:31,266 --> 00:33:32,066
And this.

538
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:33,600
One.

539
00:33:34,366 --> 00:33:35,166
Two.

540
00:33:35,500 --> 00:33:36,300
Step right.

541
00:33:37,100 --> 00:33:37,900
One.

542
00:33:42,733 --> 00:33:43,533
I'll adjust.

543
00:33:44,566 --> 00:33:45,366
Like this.

544
00:33:45,366 --> 00:33:46,200
Yes, this side.

545
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:48,566
You must stand elegantly.

546
00:33:49,300 --> 00:33:51,266
Straighten your back.

547
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,711
You are the male lead of Likay,

548
00:33:53,711 --> 00:33:58,251
You need to dance beautifully,
then people will like and follow us.

549
00:33:58,910 --> 00:34:00,598
I think dancing is really important.

550
00:34:01,460 --> 00:34:04,957
Being male lead of Likay is not only singing,

551
00:34:04,957 --> 00:34:08,001
but also performing and acting.

552
00:34:09,572 --> 00:34:10,505
Like our father.

553
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:13,500
Be tense, Guy.

554
00:34:23,166 --> 00:34:25,224
Is staying Petchprakai that bad?

555
00:34:25,883 --> 00:34:29,109
Even I give you all?
I taught you to sing, dancing, and everything

556
00:34:29,109 --> 00:34:30,266
To make you a good male lead of Likay.

557
00:34:30,300 --> 00:34:31,366
But i don't want to.

558
00:34:31,966 --> 00:34:32,989
If that is good,

559
00:34:34,003 --> 00:34:35,645
just go and stay there.

560
00:34:36,304 --> 00:34:38,116
Since you don't want to stay with Petchprakai anyway.

561
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:48,600
I was stupid back then.

562
00:34:50,900 --> 00:34:52,366
I only focused on my path,

563
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:56,600
and not be open-minded

564
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:58,800
To accept that our paths are different.

565
00:35:01,500 --> 00:35:02,933
I am never getting mad at you.

566
00:35:05,366 --> 00:35:06,700
I know that you were scared

567
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:11,200
Scared that i might get hurt like you were.

568
00:35:12,766 --> 00:35:13,566
Yes.

569
00:35:15,700 --> 00:35:17,755
I just want you to be safe.
I just want you to stay away from pain.

570
00:35:18,769 --> 00:35:19,987
But I forget that

